comments: The original version of this song was titled Wandering in the Darkness .  The title was changed to "When You Go Walking" and was credited to two unrelated songwriters on their album.  It was nominated for Bluegrass Song of the Year by the IBMA in 1996.  It caused quite a controversy at the awards show when the actual songwriter, Roy McMillan , heard the other songwriters names being announced.  To this day it is still often miscredited.
